StoryAsset.name: New Draw First and New Won Second PostMatch

keyValuePair.Value: Did that second leg go exactly according to plan?
It looked pretty close to call after the draw in the first leg. But your boys came good today and you've qualified. Did things go according to plan for you?
We handled their threat.

We're very happy. In the first leg, we saw enough to be confident we'd be able to nullify their forward players in the return fixture. That's what happened and it gave us the platform to go on and play our football. We deserved this win.
A very professional display.
A very professional display.
I think the two teams probably took a good look at each other in the first leg. Definitely, we had a plan for today and it worked out well for us. Now let's see how far we can go.
It's a chance to prove ourselves now.

I'm glad we've won today and I'm very glad we've qualified. I think this team has got real potential as an attacking force. Going through means the lads will have a chance now to show everybody what they're capable of.

I'm glad we've won today and I'm very glad we've qualified. I think this team has got real potential as an attacking force. Going through means the lads will have a chance now to show everybody what they're capable of.
Can your boys reach the Final now?
Your boys looked stronger and stronger over the course of the tie. A decent draw in the first leg and now this victory to take you into the semi-finals. How far can your team go?
We'll always be competitive.

We deserve to be in the semis. We showed great spirit today. I think we can be genuinely competitive against any team now. I want our lads in there to perform like they did here on a consistent basis. Then we might really achieve something.
We can't afford to dwell on this.

Of course everybody connected with the club is very happy we're into the semi-final. But we can't think this is something worth celebrating yet. We've shown in this tie that we're good enough to go all the way.
There's real self-belief in this team.

Confidence is so important for any team. We've got a good spirit here at %1s. When we're able to get into a rhythm like we did today, I think we're pretty difficult to play against. I think getting to the semis is something the lads can be proud of. And we all believe that there's plenty more to come.
How proud will you be to lead %1s out for the Final?
Nobody can argue that %1s don't deserve a place in the Final. The team seems to have met every challenge it's faced so far. How confident are you the boys can go on and win the %2s now?
Let's make sure we're ready!

I'm very proud of the team. We finished off the job really well today. If we play with that intensity and that fluency in the Final, I don't think we'll have anything to fear. We have to be ready for the challenge.
The Final is something to look forward to.

Great performance today and we deserved the win that put us through. Of course we'll look forward to it but, for now, we just have to put the Final to one side. We've a lot of other games to play before then and we have to be properly prepared for every one of them.
The boys deserve it.

This is where %1s want to be: competing in finals! We've done so well to get this far. If we can make ourselves as difficult to play against as we were today, we have to be in with a chance of lifting the trophy. The boys deserve their chance.
Was that a display you can be proud of?
You needed the win today to make it through to the next round and everything seemed to go according to plan. Are you starting to wonder how far your boys can go in the competition?
It's about being up for the battle.

I'm really pleased we're through. We deserved it after the way we approached the game today, fighting for every ball and keeping calm when we were under pressure. If the boys match that level of commitment in every game now, this team can really achieve something.
It's great to go through but this is only the start.

I want this team to develop a real hunger for success. So, yes, we'll celebrate going through after today's victory. But we need everybody's focus now to be on the next game. Winning has to become a habit.

I want this team to develop a real hunger for success. So, yes, we'll celebrate going through after today's victory. But we need everybody's focus now to be on the next game. Winning has to become a habit.
The boys deserve all the credit.

These were two difficult games against a good opponent. I thought the lads were positive, driving forwards in both legs of the tie. They were excellent in possession today. All credit to them. They deserve to be in the next round.
